Answer.feedback: The scoring system seems more accurate when it's asking for a very specific item (trader joes low carb cheese puffs 1.8 oz) and there is clearly only one 100% correct result. It seems to struggle more with things like furniture or clothes, where there might be many items that fit (sweatshirt blue 4xl) - that's when I seem to get lower scores even though all the product attributes match - it seems to get a good score you have to find the one specific product it already has in mind, and if you don't you will get a lower score even if it fits the criteria
